{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.33",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 33,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 33",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 33 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:1",
      "text": "“ However, Job, please hear my speech, and listen to all my words.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:2",
      "text": "See now, I have opened my mouth. My tongue has spoken in my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:3",
      "text": "My words will utter the uprightness of my heart. That which my lips know they will speak sincerely.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:4",
      "text": "The Spirit of God has made me, and the breath of the Almighty gives me life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:5",
      "text": "If you can, answer me. Set your words in order before me, and stand up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:6",
      "text": "Behold, I am toward God even as you are. I am also formed out of the clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:7",
      "text": "Behold, my terror will not make you afraid, neither will my pressure be heavy on you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:8",
      "text": "“ Surely you have spoken in my hearing, I have heard the voice of your words, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:9",
      "text": "‘ I am clean, without disobedience. I am innocent, neither is there iniquity in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:10",
      "text": "Behold, he finds occasions against me. He counts me for his enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:11",
      "text": "He puts my feet in the stocks. He marks all my paths.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:12",
      "text": "“ Behold, I will answer you. In this you are not just, for God is greater than man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:13",
      "text": "Why do you strive against him, because he doesn’t give account of any of his matters?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:14",
      "text": "For God speaks once, yes twice, though man pays no attention.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:15",
      "text": "In a dream, in a vision of the night, when deep sleep falls on men, in slumbering on the bed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:16",
      "text": "then he opens the ears of men, and seals their instruction,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:17",
      "text": "that he may withdraw man from his purpose, and hide pride from man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:18",
      "text": "He keeps back his soul from the pit, and his life from perishing by the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:19",
      "text": "“ He is chastened also with pain on his bed, with continual strife in his bones,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:20",
      "text": "so that his life abhors bread, and his soul dainty food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:21",
      "text": "His flesh is so consumed away that it can ’t be seen. His bones that were not seen stick out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:22",
      "text": "Yes, his soul draws near to the pit, and his life to the destroyers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:23",
      "text": "“ If there is beside him an angel, an interpreter, one among a thousand, to show to man what is right for him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:24",
      "text": "then God is gracious to him, and says, ‘ Deliver him from going down to the pit, I have found a ransom.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:25",
      "text": "His flesh will be fresher than a child ’s. He returns to the days of his youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:26",
      "text": "He prays to God, and he is favorable to him, so that he sees his face with joy. He restores to man his righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:27",
      "text": "He sings before men, and says, ‘ I have sinned, and perverted that which was right, and it didn’t profit me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:28",
      "text": "He has redeemed my soul from going into the pit. My life will see the light.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:29",
      "text": "“ Behold, God does all these things, twice, yes three times, with a man,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:30",
      "text": "to bring back his soul from the pit, that he may be enlightened with the light of the living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:31",
      "text": "Mark well, Job, and listen to me. Hold your peace, and I will speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:32",
      "text": "If you have anything to say, answer me. Speak, for I desire to justify you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.33.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:33",
      "text": "If not, listen to me. Hold your peace, and I will teach you wisdom.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
